Cook beef in skillet until browned. Pour off fat. Mix beef, 1/2 can soup, Worcestershire and vegetables in 2-quart shallow baking dish. Mix water, margarine and remaining soup in saucepan. Heat to a boil. Remove from heat. Stir in milk. Slowly stir in potatoes. Spoon potatoes over beef mixture. Bake at 400 degrees F 20 minutes or until hot.